race.description: Ray White Ipswich Fillies & Mares Class 3 Handicap
race.comment: BEFORE ANYONE ELSE (10) loves it here around the Ipswich circuit with two wins and a second from just three spins and will be high on confidence following that last-start victory. Looks the runner in this field with the most upside and can go right on with the job now. The well-related WILD GYPSY (4) (half to G1 winner Wild Ruler) is a former NSW galloper having her first run for the new stable but should find this easier than what she faced down south. Can run a big race while fresh. ROSE NOIR (5) has placed three from three over this track and trip and has a solid first-up record. Worth including in calculations. DREAM LANTERN (3) has won two from three when fresh and must be considered for the multiples. CUTEPI (2) next in line with the claim from the inside marble.
